  <title translate="true">Simple Model: Solver</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Simple Model: Solver</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This model uses the SIP solver. &#160;To use it select </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Model|MODFLOW Packages and Programs</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">. Expand the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Solvers</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and check the radio button for the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">SIP</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> package. &#160;Change </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">MXITER</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 50, </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">IPCALC</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 0, and </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">WSEED</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to 0.001. Then click </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">OK</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> to close the dialog box.</text></para>
  </body>
</topic>
